
    A 43-year-old woman was arrested for allegedly defrauding a
medical equipment company out of more than R460m, the Hawks said on Thursday.The woman was arrested on Wednesday at the Hawks’ Commercial
Crime Unit office in Germiston, east of Johannesburg, following a three-month
investigation, spokesperson Captain Ndivhuwo Mulamu said in a statement.Mulamu said the woman was an accountant for the company and
had allegedly duplicated payments by transferring money into her late husband’s
